'''Head of Administration''' is the official title for appointed or elected head of a local government in [[Russia|Russian Federation]].<ref>Constitution of the Russian Federation: [http://www.constitution.ru/en/10003000-07.htm Constitution of the Russian Federation]</ref><ref>[http://www.government.ru/archiv/data/static_text.html-he_id_785.htm Federal Law on the Government of the Russian Federation]</ref> In many Federal Districts, regions and cities, the position as Head of Administration is the equivalent to that of the [[Mayor]], [[Governor (Russia)|Governor]], or the Head of local government.

