'''hr-skyline''' was a German, public [[radio station]] owned and operated by the [[Hessischer Rundfunk]] (HR).
==History== The main focus of the program was on economic reporting. To underline this focus, the broadcasting studio of ''hr-skyline'' was located in Frankfurt's [[Bankenviertel]] on the 54th floor of the [[Main Tower]]. The follow-up program [[hr-info]] has taken over this focus in part, but is increasingly aimed at sports and culture lovers.
