The '''Marshal of the Holy Roman Church and Sacred Conclave''' was a hereditary official in the [[Pontifical Household]] before Pope Paul VI's reform of the [[papal court]] in his [[motu proprio]] ''[[Pontificalis Domus]]'' of 1968.  It was vested in Prince [[House of Chigi|Chigi]], prince of Farnese, Campagnano, etc., etc.  During the [[Papal conclave|conclave]], the Marshal had the ceremonial duty of sealing the doors to the [[Sistine Chapel]] from the outside.

