The '''National Rally for Democracy in Chad''' ({{lang-fr|Rassemblement national pour la démocratie au Tchad - le Réveil}}) is a [[political party]] in [[Chad]]. It is considered a moderate opposition party allied with the ruling [[Patriotic Salvation Movement]] (MPS),<ref>[http://www.primature-tchad.org/?2007/08/30/580-du-concret "Du concrêt"], Chadian government website, August 30, 2007 {{fr icon}}.</ref> and it participates in the government.

In the [[Chadian parliamentary election, 2002|parliamentary election]] held on 21 April 2002, the party won one out of 155 seats.<ref>[http://www.ipu.org/parline-e/reports/2061_E.htm 2002 election results], IPU PARLINE.</ref> In the [[Chadian presidential election, 2006|May 2006 presidential election]], its candidate, [[Albert Pahimi Padacké]], won 7.82% of the vote.<ref>Valery Gottingar, [http://www.primature-tchad.org/?2006/05/29/180-scrutin-presidentiel-du-03-mai-2006-le-conseil-constitutionnel-proclame-le-president-idriss-deby-itno-reelu-au-premier-tour-avec-un-score-de-6467 "Scrutin présidentiel du 03 mai 2006: le Conseil Constitutionnel proclame le Président Idriss Deby Itno réélu au premier tour avec un score de 64,67%."], Chadian government website, May 29, 2006 {{fr icon}}.</ref>

