The '''Diocese of Gallese''' (Latin: ''Dioecesis Gallesina'') was a Roman Catholic diocese located in the town of [[Gallese]] near the city of [[Viterbo]] in the [[Province of Viterbo]]. In 1805, it was united with the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Civita Castellana|Diocese of Civita Castellana e Orte]] to form the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Civita Castellana|Diocese of Civita Castellana, Orte e Gallese]].<ref name=CathHierGallese>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dg202.html "Diocese of Gallese"] ''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''. David M. Cheney. Retrieved May 1, 2016{{Self-published source|date=January 2017}}</ref><ref name=GCathGallese>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/former/t0828.htm "Titular Episcopal See of Gallese"] ''GCatholic.org''. Gabriel Chow. Retrieved May 1, 2016</ref> It was restored as a Titular Episcopal See in 1991.<ref name=GCathGallese />

